@drcrallen 

Is your benchmark easily reproducible on TPC-H? (E.g., do you have it scripted...?)

We would be interested in re-running your benchmark and doing some analysis. Specifically, we would be interested in targeting the contribution of the bitmaps to the running time and see where the hot spots are.

@lemire : yes, that is exactly why regex topN was chosen as one of the test cases. In that case the underlying engine does a TON of unions of underlying bitmaps. And, as expected, roaring pulls notably ahead of concise in execution time. It is suspected that evaluating the regex takes a significant chunk time in this type of query (but I don't have profiling to back that up yet).

What is notably lacking from my prior test is a case with filtering, which I'm working on spinning up now.

For anyone else reading this thread, please note that these are intended to be _data points_ not final conclusions. I'll update my prior post to make that a little clearer.
